-- Investors Open 5.1% Fewer China Stock Trading Accounts Week Ended July 2
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-06T23:32:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/investors-open-5-1-fewer-china-stock-trading-accounts-week-ended-july-2.html

          
          
             Investors opened 5.1 percent fewer
accounts to trade Chinese stocks during the week ended July 2 as
compared with a week earlier, according to the China Securities
Depository and Clearing Corp.  
 Investors opened 277,833 accounts during the week,
according to the clearing house.  
